        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient has a confirmed diagnosis of HF based on a HF admission and/or a clear
             diagnosis of HF and/or reduced ejection fraction (â‰¤45% measured by echocardiography
             within the last six months);

          -  Patient is referred to cardiac rehabilitation program;

          -  Patient is willing to attend an onsite cardiac rehabilitation program twice weekly for
             12 weeks;

          -  In the opinion of the referring physician, the patient is medically stable, and able
             to participate in an exercise program

          -  Patient is able, in the opinion of the qualified investigator, to comprehend and
             participate in the exercise intervention;

          -  Patient is 18 years of age or older;

          -  Patient is willing to provide informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient is unable to read and understand English or French

          -  Patient intends to begin cardiac rehabilitation within the next 6 weeks

          -  Patient is unwilling or unable to return for follow-up visits at 12 and 26 weeks;

          -  Patient is currently using Nordic Walking poles.
